; Parser test: comments and whitespace handling
; Expected: 0 errors; all comments highlighted as comments

; This is a semicolon full-line comment

# This is a hash full-line comment

; ── Transaction with inline comment on header ──
2026-03-01 Groceries  ; weekly shopping
    expenses:food:groceries             $45.00
    assets:bank:checking

; ── Posting with inline comment ──
2026-03-02 Coffee
    expenses:food:coffee                 $4.50  ; morning latte
    assets:cash

; ── Blank lines separate transactions ──

2026-03-03 First
    expenses:misc                       $10.00
    assets:cash

2026-03-03 Second
    expenses:misc                       $20.00
    assets:cash

; ── comment/end comment block ──
; Everything between these keywords is ignored by the parser

comment
This entire block is a comment.
It can contain anything: dates, amounts, random text.
2026-99-99 This is NOT parsed as a transaction
    not:a:real:posting  $999
Even directive keywords like "account" are ignored here.
end comment

; ── Transaction after comment block should parse normally ──
2026-03-04 After comment block
    expenses:food                       $15.00
    assets:bank:checking

; ── Mixed comments between transactions ──
; This comment separates transactions
# So does this one
2026-03-05 Final transaction
    expenses:shopping                   $50.00
    assets:bank:checking
